ExecDesc.value: CA ARCserve Backup Message Engine Denial of Service (IPv6 Version)

EngDesc.value: A denial of service vulnerability exists in CA ARCserve Backup Message Engine. The vulnerability is due to insufficient data validation. A remote unauthenticated attacker may exploit this vulnerability by sending a crafted message to the target server. A successful attack could create a denial of service condition to the Message Engine service. (IPv6 Version)
